<item>
            <title>[LU-8531] Times on lustre filesystem are wrong and won&apos;t update</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8531</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After crashing the mds on the lustre file system lscratche, upon recovery it was found that the top level dates are wrong. Even after running chmod neither the Modify or Change times were updated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;oslic2 ~&amp;gt; stat /p/lscratche
 File: `/p/lscratche&apos;
Size: 609792          Blocks: 1191       IO Block: 131072 directory
Device: 68756a28h/1752525352d   Inode: 144115188193296385  Links: 3912
Access: (0755/drwxr-xr-x)  Uid: (    0/    root)   Gid: (    0/    root)
Access: 1969-12-31 16:00:00.000000000 -0800
Modify: 1969-12-31 16:00:00.000000000 -0800
Change: 2248-08-12 09:46:20.000000000 -0700
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>lustre-2.5.5-6chaos_2.6.32_573.26.1.1chaos.ch5.4.x86_64.x86_64</environment>
        <key id="39075">LU-8531</key>
            <summary>Times on lustre filesystem are wrong and won&apos;t update</summary>
